🔵 What is Bitnami?
Bitnami is a library of pre-packaged, ready-to-deploy applications and Helm charts maintained by VMware (now part of Broadcom).
Think of it like an App Store for Kubernetes — instead of building everything from scratch, you use Bitnami's pre-built, production-ready charts.


Add a Helm Chart Repository
We'll deploy Nginx as a sample app using the official Bitnami repo:

# Add Bitnami repo
helm repo add bitnami https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami

# Update repo
helm repo update

Create a Namespace

kubectl create namespace myapp

Deploy Nginx via Helm

helm install myapp-release bitnami/nginx \
  --namespace myapp \
  --set service.type=LoadBalancer \
  --set replicaCount=2

Flag                          Meaning
---------------------------------------------------------
myapp-release                 Your Helm release name
bitnami/nginx                 Chart from Bitnami repo
--namespace myapp             Deploy into myapp namespace
service.type=LoadBalancer     AWS will create an ELB
replicaCount=2                2 pods running

Verify Deployment

# Check Helm release
helm list -n myapp

# Check pods
kubectl get pods -n myapp

# Check service & get LoadBalancer URL
kubectl get svc -n myapp

Useful Helm Commands

# See all deployed releases
helm list -n myapp

# Check history of a release
helm history myapp-release -n myapp

# Upgrade a release (e.g change replicas)
helm upgrade myapp-release bitnami/nginx \
  --namespace myapp \
  --set replicaCount=3

# Rollback to previous version
helm rollback myapp-release 1 -n myapp

🧹 Cleanup

# Uninstall Helm release
helm uninstall myapp-release -n myapp

# Delete namespace
kubectl delete namespace myapp

